//
// test/preprocess/p03/fail.test — P3 undefined-macro fixture per
// the FR-037 locked diagnostic strings in
// `specs/002-m1-lex-preprocess/contracts/diagnostic-output.contract.md`
// + the "Mandatory diagnostic-string fixtures" table.
//
// FR-037 P3 lock:  `undefined macro reference: '%<NAME>%'`  (warning)
//
// Per Constitution Principle VIII the fixture asserts the EXACT
// diagnostic string. The string itself is locked; the severity was
// downgraded from Error to Warning in the 2026-05-04 contract
// amendment so the M5 `NSLCheckSemanticsPass` (slot 6) can surface
// the canonical residue diagnostic at MLIR-emit time without the M1
// phase short-circuiting the pipeline.
//
// `nslc -emit=tokens` exits 0 (warning is non-fatal) and emits the
// token stream to stdout; the warning text appears on stderr.

// RUN: echo 'reg x = %%UNDEF%%;' > %t.nsl
// RUN: %nslc -emit=tokens %t.nsl 2>&1 | FileCheck %s

// FR-037 LOCKED STRING — exact match (severity warning post-amendment):
// CHECK: warning: undefined macro reference: '%UNDEF%'
